    "As motivation for the following definition, recall the discussion of regular open algebras and subalgebras thereof in Remark 2.15.Definition 5.4 (Underlying BAO).",
    "Given a possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩, its underlying BAO is the algebra F b = ⟨A, ∧, -, ⊤, {■ i } i∈I ⟩ where:1.",
    "X ∧ Y = X ∩ Y; 3.",
    "-X = int(S \\ X); 31 4.",
    "■ i Y = {x ∈ S | R i (x) ⊆ Y }."
